               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><title>Commentaries on Old Testament books fol. 3r-241r</title>
                  <textLang xml:lang="am"/>
                     <note>Commentary on Proverbs, fol. 3r-21v; commentary on Wisdom of Solomon, fol. 22r-39v; commentary on Ecclesiastes, fol. 39v-50r; commentary on Daniel, fol. 50r-69v; commentary on 4 Ezra, fol. 69v-94v; commentary on Hosea, fol. 94v-104v; commentary on Amos, fol. 104v-110r; commentary on Micah, fol. 110r-115r; commentary on Joel, fol. 115r-118v; commentary on Obadiah, fol. 118v-119v; commentary on Jonah, fol. 119v-121r; commentary on Nahum, fol. 121r-123v; commentary on Habakkuk, fol. 123v-128v; commentary on Zephaniah, fol. 128v-129v; commentary on Haggai, fol. 130r-131v; commentary on Zechariah, fol. 131v-141r; commentary on Malachi, fol. 141r-143r; commentary on Jeremiah, fol. 149r-170v; commentary on Baruch, fol. 170v-171r; commentary on Lamentations, fol. 171r-174v; commentary on the Letter of Jeremiah, fol. 174v-175r; commentary on the Prophecy to Pashur, fol. 175rv; commentary on 4 Baruch, fol. 175v-178v; commentary on Job, fol. 178v-210r; commentary on 1 Maccabees, fol. 213r-219v; commentary on 2 Maccabees, fol. 219v-221v; commentary on 3 Maccabees, fol. 222r-223v; commentary on Tobit, fol. 223v-228r; commentary on Judith, fol. 228r-234v; commentary on Esther, fol. 234v-241r
                        
                     </note></msItem>
                  
